# SEO & branding (assets, routing, verification)

Apply on **every** substantive change involving **UI, assets, copy, or metadata** (not only new pages). **New route `layout.tsx`, `pageMetadata()`, and `BreadcrumbJsonLd`:** see `seo-new-pages.mdc`.

## 1. Asset naming, alt text & 3D (critical)

- **File names**: All **new** images and model assets use hybrid naming: `[r-series]-cobot-[fr-model].[ext]`.
- **Alt text**: Every `<Image />` or `<img>` must include `alt` via i18n key lookup (`t('image_alt_key')` style). Do **not** hardcode Chinese or English alt strings inline.
- **Alt text copy standard**: The translation value behind that key should follow `[r-series] ([fr-model]) Collaborative Robot for [Context]` (replace placeholders with real series, model, and page-specific context).
- **3D / Canvas**: For Canvas or 3D viewers, set `aria-label` or an equivalent `description` prop so the robotic arm model is described for assistive tech.

### GLB preload (Lighthouse / production parity)

- **Single pattern**: On each **segment `layout.tsx` that mounts `<model-viewer>`**, add `ModelViewerScript` from `@/components/ModelViewerScript.tsx` and `GlbPreloadLinks`. Do **not** load `model-viewer.min.js` from root `ClientLayout` (avoids chunk preload warnings on text-only pages). Attributes stay aligned with `preloadGlb()` in `@/lib/glb-cache.ts` and `GLB_MIME_TYPE` in `@/lib/glb-preload-constants.ts` (`rel="preload"`, `as="fetch"`, `type="model/gltf-binary"`, `crossOrigin="anonymous"`). **Do not** also call `preloadGlb()` from pages when that layout already emits `GlbPreloadLinks` (duplicate fetch/noise).
- **Paths**: Add every new hero/showcase model to `cobotGlbModels` (and related maps) in `@/data/products.ts`, then reference those same URL strings in `GlbPreloadLinks` / `GLB_PRELOAD_*` exports—**never** duplicate ad-hoc paths.
- **Scope**: Preload only the `.glb` files actually used on that route (e.g. home: r-Lite + r-Max; Advisor / r-Lite detail: r-Lite only). When adding **R-Max** (or other) product pages with 3D, extend `GlbPreloadLinks` usage on that segment’s layout the same way.

## 2. Metadata (when editing titles or descriptions)

- **Title**: Must include **Cobot** and **Robotic Arm**. Use `seoTitle()` from `@/lib/site-seo.ts` where a title is set or overridden.
- **Description**: Must be **unique** per page where applicable, include **brand keywords**, and use `seoDescription()` when the helper should append missing required phrases.

## 3. Routing & IA

- **No redundancy**: Avoid generic paths like `/arm`. Prefer `/cobots/r-core` or other specific product paths.
- **Applications**: Prefer industry-specific, long-tail framing (e.g. Medical, Lab, Manufacturing) in URLs, copy, and metadata where it matches IA.
- **Localized links required**: Any **new** link generated from `app/**` must preserve language-prefix logic (`/zh/...` and `/en/...`). Never introduce raw non-prefixed links like `/about` that can become dead links in localized navigation.

## 4. Sitemap, robots & hreflang (technical)

- **Sitemap / robots**: Implemented via `app/sitemap.ts` and `app/robots.ts`; URL list lives in `lib/site-paths.ts` — **add every new indexable path** there (must cover all `/cobots/*` and `/applications/*` pages).
- **Production URL**: Set `NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL` (no trailing slash) so sitemap, robots, and hreflang absolute URLs match the live domain.
- **Hreflang**: Route layouts pass a pathname into `pageMetadata(..., pathname)` so Next emits `link rel="alternate" hreflang="zh-CN|en-US|x-default"`. Language variants use physical subdirectory routes `/zh/*` and `/en/*` (see `middleware.ts`); crawlers and shared links should always use the prefixed language URL.
- **GEO integrity**: For every new indexable page, ensure metadata keeps `alternates` with `/zh` and `/en` counterparts so geo-language ranking signals stay paired.

## 5. Verification

- After meaningful UI or SEO-affecting changes, **remind the user** to run Lighthouse (SEO category) and aim for **100/100** where feasible.
